+# v0.14 Backup Status Tracking
+
+Date: 2026-06-09
+Phase: backup status tracking preview
+Status: PASS for local receipt, GitHub push, Drive-folder backup, and vault report status reflection
+
+## Goal
+
+When a backup command says work was backed up, matching local records should also remember that state in `backup_status`.
+
+## Added Behavior
+
+| Area | Change |
+|---|---|
+| Local receipt | `backup receipt` updates `backup_status.local=complete` |
+| GitHub backup | `backup github --push` updates `backup_status.github=complete` |
+| GitHub package only | `backup github` without `--push` keeps `backup_status.github=pending` |
+| Drive backup | `backup drive` updates `backup_status.google_drive=complete` |
+| Records | Updated records persist back to their JSON files |
+| Vault report | `report vault` reflects local/GitHub/Drive status counts |
+
+## Commands
+
+```powershell
+python .\pala.py backup receipt --all
+python .\pala.py backup drive --all --target .\data\backups\drive-status-smoke
+python .\pala.py backup github --all --knowledge-bank <repo> --push
+python .\pala.py report vault --all --json
+```
+
+## Smoke Test
+
+Executed in `C:\Users\Pala-Home-1\Desktop\Codex\pala-memory-core`:
+
+```powershell
+python -m py_compile .\pala.py
+python .\pala.py backup receipt --all
+python .\pala.py backup drive --all --target .\data\backups\drive-status-smoke-<stamp>
+python .\pala.py backup github --all --knowledge-bank <local-temp-git-repo> --push
+python .\pala.py report vault --all --json
+```
+
+Observed key output:
+
+```text
+receipt saved data\backups\2026-06-09-backup-receipt.md
+backup_status.local=complete updated=8
+drive backup package saved ...\pala-memory-core-all-drive-backup
+records=8 artifacts=3
+backup_status.google_drive=complete updated=8
+github backup package saved ...\pala-memory-core-all-backup
+records=8 artifacts=3 committed=True pushed=True
+backup_status.github=complete updated=8
+```
+
+Observed vault status after push smoke:
+
+```json
+"backup_status": {
+  "local": { "complete": 8 },
+  "github": { "complete": 8 },
+  "google_drive": { "complete": 8 }
+}
+```
+
+## Release Posture
+
+This is a local status-tracking preview. It updates local record JSON files after backup commands succeed. It does not yet reconcile backup status from remote GitHub/Drive independently after the fact.
diff --git a/pala.py b/pala.py
index 7f204e1..9941a1f 100644
--- a/pala.py
+++ b/pala.py
@@ -229,6 +229,41 @@ def load_records(date: str | None = None) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:
     return [read_record_json(path) for path in paths]
 
 
+def record_json_path(record: dict[str, Any]) -> Path | None:
+    json_path = record.get("_json_path")
+    if not json_path:
+        return None
+    path = (ROOT / str(json_path)).resolve()
+    if path == ROOT or ROOT in path.parents:
+        return path
+    return None
+
+
+def persist_record(record: dict[str, Any]) -> bool:
+    path = record_json_path(record)
+    if not path:
+        return False
+    stored = {key: value for key, value in record.items() if not key.startswith("_")}
+    path.write_text(json.dumps(stored, indent=2, ensure_ascii=True), encoding="utf-8")
+    return True
+
+
+def update_backup_status(records: list[dict[str, Any]], key: str, status: str, receipt: str) -> int:
+    updated = 0
+    backed_up_at = now_utc().isoformat()
+    for record in records:
+        backup_status = record.setdefault("backup_status", {})
+        backup_status.setdefault("local", "complete")
+        backup_status.setdefault("github", "pending")
+        backup_status.setdefault("google_drive", "pending")
+        backup_status[key] = status
+        backup_status["last_backup_at"] = backed_up_at
+        backup_status["receipt"] = receipt
+        if persist_record(record):
+            updated += 1
+    return updated
+
+
 def load_today_records() -> list[dict[str, Any]]:
     return load_records(today())
 
